content.description: A sustained, sharp, and technical face that is located in a gulley on the right side of the trail that leads to St. Louis Direct and Shredder Wall. Climb up the first few bolts below small bulge and pull slightly left on grey rock. Â Climb on a few larger holds with bigger moves after last bolt to chains.
content.location: Walk 20 yards up the trail on the way to St. Louis Direct and Shredder wall. A small side trail veering right into a steep gulley with homemade steps will lead to the climb.

content.description: Start up some blocky face moves to gain the prominent arete, the work your way up using the arete, face holds, or bear hug the whole tower. Step left at the top to clip the chains on the left side of arete. Chains are not in the greatest spot.
content.location: This route heads up the striking arete, can't miss it as it is the only line on the wall.

climbs.name: Short on Time, High on Lime

content.description: A very unique climb for Rattler. Climb up thin, slabby face avoiding the loose crack to the right. Pull through awesome sequence at the bulge into a proper, but short finger crack section before the chains.
content.protection: 7 bolts. Rap rings on the anchor. An alpine/extended draw is nice for the third bolt.

content.description: PIC stands alone from the other climbs in the area, downhill on small section of good grey rock that is a bit steeper than it appears. Sequential and balancey moves on crimps, sidepulls, and underclings, and a very thought provoking crux. This is a new route so be careful for some fragile chert knobs. Well protected and safe, a good moderate to check out.
content.location: Located downhill from St. Louis Direct and the Shredder Wall. It is on the same fin of rock as St. Louis Direct. Follow the wall downhill on the north side and you will see it.
